reviews.review: I had a very low expectation for this movie due to reviews and movie critics. However, it was very enjoyable and I'd watch it again.

I thought it was a great finale to the last trilogy. Kylo Ren's character was true to form and tragic. Rey's character finally had the exposition she deserved, I just wish it would have been exposed and brought out over the last two films. Warrants another viewing.

This movie felt so chopped up it hurt not to mention character interaction was so unnatural. One minute someone is about to get there head blown off the next there being asked by the same person who wants to see them dead to run away with them.

After reading multiple reviews about how "horrendous," this movie was, I had little hope. Upon seeing the movie for myself, along with my father who grew up with the original trilogy, we both agreed this surpassed our expectations tenfold. My only issues were how fast paced the first half of the film was, but considering the plot had hardly moved after episode 8, I understand why J.J. Abrams had to rush the exposition and plot forward. The film was entertaining all throughout, filled with well written humor, and had just the right amount of nostalgic fan service.

A very disappointed end to what could have been a very impactful trilogy. The Last Jedi set expectations high and laid the ground work for something extremely compelling and meaningful. Instead, we got lackluster storytelling and appalling and unjustified character choices that undermine an entire trilogy worth of character development.

The writing is lazy and sloppy, several main characters are thrown away the second the plot has no use for them, and because of the terrible writing hardly any of the characters get to have any emotion or humanity (the acting is excellent the fault lies with the script).
Muy mala!!!! Solo rellenaron la historia!!!
Sensational. A thrilling, satisfying and worthy ending to the saga.

The movie was both entertaining and exceeded my expectations . I'm reasonably satisfied on how the many,many story lines were rapped up.  While Empire Strikes back is still the Gold Standard of Star Wars films, and this film is NOWHERE close to that standard,   I still think critics were unduly harsh on the film.
